    }
    boolean getsWet = isRaining && !hasUmbrella;
    System.out.println("Is it raining? " + isRaining);
    System.out.println("Does person have umbrella? " + hasUmbrella);
    System.out.println("Does person get wet? " + getsWet);
  }
}",

If the probability of carrying an umbrella is changed to always (e.g., 1.0), does this guarantee the person will not get wet?
